OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773667699
OL,3,CTrash tracker: Where does Birmingham's
OL,4,Crubbish actually end up?
OL,6,FThe figures show most of the rubbish
OL,7,Fwe tracked ended up in Tyseley -
OL,8,Fwhere, of course, the city's main
OL,9,Fincinerator is based. We already know
OL,10,Fthat Birmingham City Council burns the
OL,11,Fvast majority of its waste - figures
OL,12,Fobtained by ITV News Central last year
OL,13,Frevealed it's roughly 81%.
OL,15,FAnd despite a stated ambition to
OL,16,Freduce reliance on it, at the end of
OL,17,F2024, the council signed a new 10-year
OL,18,Fcontract for Veolia to continue
OL,19,Fproviding waste services, including
OL,20,Fthe incinerator, worth some #426
OL,21,Fmillion.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
